<section id="To_create_a_method1" remap="TID_15614">
	<title>Creating a Method</title>
	<para>
		This procedure shows you how to create a method.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Create a Method</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Automate</guimenu><guisubmenu>Explorer</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, navigate to the class where you want to create a method.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>Methods</guilabel> tab.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Configuration)</guilabel>, 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2360.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guilabel>(Add a New Method)</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In the <guilabel>Main Info</guilabel> area, type in a <guilabel>Name</guilabel> and <guilabel>Display Name</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step> 
		<!--step>
			<para>
				Select a language for the method, either perl or ruby.
			</para>
		</step-->
		<step>
			<para>
				For <guilabel>Location</guilabel>, select <guimenuitem>inline</guimenuitem>. Once selected, you will be presented with a <guilabel>Data</guilabel> area in which to write or copy the script.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guilabel>Validate</guilabel> to check the syntax.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure> 
